title: Grateful Dead Live at Civic Arena on 1985-07-02
lineage: Master PCM > DAW (via SEKD Prodif) > Wav > cdwav > Flac
description: Jack Straw-> It Must Have Been The Roses, Minglewood Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Cassidy, Big Railroad Blues, Promised Land Women Are Smarter-> Crazy Fingers-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Turn On Your Love Light, E:Revolution-> E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: End of tour One of the few memorable things about this end of tour show was the encore. Jerry completely forgot the opening verse to Brokedown, stopped and said "hello" then started again. Just another example of how the band can fuck up and just endear themselves further to the loyal following. I remember jumping up and down and yelling "I love you Jerry". I broke my ankle at this show.

mellow mood-- with recordings of this quality, who needs soundboards?
this is a VERY laid back show-- perfect to chill to... it has the sort of vibe you get while listening to Reckoning or Bear's Choice... (which are standards i return to again and again- for 19 years now!)
no great stand out performances, just an all around nice show with INCREDIBLE crystal clear sound!!
how do those Oades boys do it?? wow!!
Four Stars, but this is really a keeper. Just like the dude below relates, this is a very mellow, lovable, laid-back show. It's pure enjoyment, and this is the AUD with maximum warmth. Get it now.

This is a keeper, my first show. Great show this was my first.
Funny how long ago , the strange trip -good sound good night. They stopped doing the Lost Sailor •Saint of Circumstance combo soon after. Bob in a pink Alligator T-Shirt ( classic) . The encore - Jerry Garcia " Hello - sounded good didn't it . We all started playin .... Blah blah blah . "The Throwin Stones • Turn on Your Lovelight is great. The Terrapin Station is fabulous as is the whole first set. Woman are Smarter ( ManSmart Woman are Smarter) second set opener is a treat.Crazy Fingers!!!!!              Set 1

Jack Straw-> It Must Have Been The Roses, Minglewood Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Cassidy, Big Railroad Blues, Promised Land

Set 2

Women Are Smarter-> Crazy Fingers-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Turn On Your Love Light, E:Revolution-> E: Brokedown Palace

Mellow Just checked out this show after doing a few '85s from Aug./Sept, never heard this one before. A couple of folks below said it was very laid back. Set 1 has 2 slow Jerry songs but Minglewood > FOTD (a meaty version) > Cassidy > Big RR > Promised Land...not laid back at all. Maybe you guys were up in the rafters smokin dirt weed? Nice 2nd set but nothing special. Short D>S kind of an indication of a desire to get back to California. Check out the first 2 Red Rocks shows if you want a mellow 85
